  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Designers reach for Storm Grey when they want a roof that disappears into 'looks correct' rather than competing for attention. It is balanced, slightly cool, and difficult to pair badly. On a Florida house with bright sun and white stucco, it is one of the safest specifications you can write.",
      "The granule blend uses a base of charcoal granules with smaller portions of true black and storm-gray accents to keep the surface from going dead flat. In direct midday sun the texture catches enough light to show the dimensional shadow line that gives Legacy Scotchgard its premium feel.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, cream, navy, sage, and warm terra-cotta sidings. Almost any house color works underneath it."
    ],
